 exmh p content type text plain charset us ascii jason rennie writes my sysadmins have told me that the sending mail client is supposed to escape lines begining with from exmh doesn t do this should it it appears that my mh is mh does nmh fix this actually this issue used to escalate into a religious war the from envelope is an artifact of the mbox mailbox format and from that perspective it should be the mail server that stores its mailboxes in mbox format that should be responsible for escaping lines beginning with from on the other hand this breaks the assumption that the mail transport only touches the message headers and leaves the message body alone things like pgp signatures break when the mail server changes the message body also strictly speaking the mbox format envelope or for us old timers the uucp envelope isn t just any line beginning with from it s really from a single space a valid email address two spaces and a valid date for example from ptardif nbnet nb ca sun jul john abreau executive director boston linux unix im jabr jabber blu org abreauj aim abreauj yahoo icq email jabr blu org www http www abreau net pgp key id xd c b d pgp key fingerprint fb f c b d b e c a e f c be some people say the enemy of my enemy is my friend i often respond when elephants fight it s the grass that gets trampled exmh p content type application pgp signature begin pgp signature version gnupg v gnu linux comment exmh version iqcvawubpasczlv a rvx xzaqjlrgqayxnhxlayoas wtckqz pr jhtamxm s tx r ycztaak wd u zqiocr j g xn gm asvrl ipetx afhdq pg w su zycxornmqvi syaqx m m irnsdqr arkhc u zqq xumxstirc dwkk oyalefse rw mvfx end pgp signature exmh p exmh users mailing list exmh users redhat com https listman redhat com mailman listinfo exmh users 